Sir: Congratulations to President Biden’s nominee, Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson, a federal judge on the United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit, since June 2021. From 2013 until 2021, she served as a United States district judge. Furthermore, she served as a vice-chair and commissioner, on the United States Sentencing Commission until December 2014.
 
Judge Jackson is currently a member of the Judicial Conference Committee on Defender Services, as well as on the Board of Overseers of Harvard University and the Council of the American Law Institute. She also currently serves on the United States Supreme Court Fellows Commission. 